
## **Master Plan: CoinMarketCap Selenium Scraper**

### **Phase 1: Setup & Dependencies**
- • Install required packages: `selenium`, `webdriver-manager`, `requests`, `beautifulsoup4`
- • Set up Chrome WebDriver with automatic management
- • Create virtual environment and requirements.txt

### **Phase 2: Core Scraping Logic**
- • Navigate to `https://coinmarketcap.com/` using Selenium
- • Extract top 100 coins data from the main page
- • Filter out stablecoins using tag detection (USDT, USDC, BUSD, etc.)
- • Collect coin profile URLs and basic information

### **Phase 3: Individual Coin Processing**
- • Loop through each non-stablecoin coin
- • Navigate to individual coin detail pages using Selenium
- • Locate and interact with the price chart component
- • Set maximum timeframe (MAX/ALL) and enable log scale
- • Wait for chart to render completely

### **Phase 4: SVG Extraction & Processing**
- • Extract SVG chart data from the rendered page
- • Handle dynamic content loading with explicit waits
- • Capture chart in maximum timeframe with log scale.
    - To select maximun timeframe you need to click on the <li> element with attribute data-index="tab-4" witch has <h5> with text "All"
    - Then to select the log scale you need to click on the <li> element with attribute data-index="tab-5" witch has <h5> with text "LOG"

- • Store SVG content with coin metadata

### **Phase 5: HTML Table Generation**
- • Create HTML table structure with responsive design
- • Embed SVG charts directly into table cells
- • Include coin names, ranks, and other relevant data
- • Add CSS styling for better presentation

### **Phase 6: Error Handling & Optimization**
- • Implement retry mechanisms for failed requests
- • Add rate limiting to avoid being blocked
- • Handle network timeouts and page load issues
- • Add progress tracking and logging

### **Phase 7: Output & Storage**
- • Generate final HTML file with embedded charts
- • Save coin data to JSON for future reference
- • Create backup of raw SVG files
- • Implement data validation and quality checks

### **Key Technical Considerations:**
- • Use `webdriver-manager` for automatic ChromeDriver management
- • Implement explicit waits for dynamic content
- • Handle anti-bot measures with realistic delays
- • Use headless mode option for server deployment
- • Implement proper exception handling for robust operation

